Hope things are going well for you,<br>
<br>
There is a point I would like to make that hasn't really been mentioned here that I would like to bring up.<br>
<br>
A good warrior doesnt just know how to play a warrior well he also takes the time to learn the abilities of those he will group with, now I know that this has been said but this is only the first step.  The next is then to learn how to access the abilities of those you group with.  can your group effectively deal with multi pulls, do they know how to assist correctly do they know how to reduce there agro etc etc and you need to be able to access this within the first few pulls You have to remember when you in pick-up groups with people you have never grouped with before you dont know the person behind the character, so the greatest skill you can learn is the ability to access there abilities and limitations quickly.  Now this is something most would say is obvious and all warriors do this, WRONG,  I joined a group the other day in LGuk the other day that completely fell apart just because nobody had a clue, I was not the Main Tank and I wasnt the group leader and I was going to a part of the zone I had never been to before, the group got trained the leader panicked we all died and it was a very nasty CR afterwards.<br>
<br>
Anyway thats my advice, learn those skills, use them and your rep will increase no end. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubayhobumblebear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bayho Bumblebear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/20/02 6:20:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what makes a good warrior?</span><hr size=1> Basically what everyone is saying, but seem to be missing Baadan, is that you need to be a LEADER.<br>
<br>
Take the initiative to invite people to your group, do not just be a LFG person.  Get to know the zones where you hunt and raid well, take in that group or raid and lay waste to everything.  A good warrior should not only be able to call the shots in a given zone, but pull that zone.  I do not care if it is hateplane or HoT, you can pull those zones as good as any monk.  The key is knowledge.  The warrior behind the keyboard is much more important than any armor you can wear or weapons you can wield.<br>
<br>
Furor is not a great warrior because of what he wears.  Furor is a great warrior because he went into the unknown leading others, and using what he learned formed strategies that got all his friends and family back home alive.  Loot is simply a by-product of that.<br>
<br>
Best of luck, and be a LEADER.<br>
<br>
Bayho <p>Loyalty above all, except Honor.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukbern.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kbern</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/20/02 8:38:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: If you don't mind me answering ;)</span><hr size=1> Scales<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://scarecrow.clickhere2.net/images/oaksiggy_new1.gif" border=0></a><br><p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=253834">Saurakk Rex</a>
