<br>
Im usually the one afk all the time smokin.  Thats why I love Luclin mobs.<br>
<br>
Keroppi says &quot;Autoattack on, please watch out how you move the mob, Im going afk to smoke, make some coffee, use the bathroom, play some PS2 and read a book&quot;.<br>
<br>
Rooted mobs are even better <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
But, in seriousness, a lot of the comments made in this thread definitely ring true.<br>
<br>
Learn the game, the more you know about it the better off you are.  Knowledge is &gt; just about everything else.  Do you really need a monk/chanter for that pull?  Do you really need 60 people for that kill?<br>
<br>
A self sufficient warrior is a very valuable commodity.  Find items/means to make yourself very mobile and very versatile.<br>
<br>
As well, always be aware of what is going on around you.  When is that spawn going to pop?  What order are you killing those mobs?  Which mobs are best to break mez on before others?  Which should you kill before the others if you have multiple mobs being tanked and are unmezzable?  How should you position that mob to get the best DPS out of your guild while you are MTing it?  How do you position that mob?  What spots in your current area are BAD BAD warp spots if the mob gets stuck there?<br>
<br>
Above all else though, be nice to other people.  Help them out.  Realize that this is just a game, and as a community, how you play the game does not only affect your own personal enjoyment in it, it has the potential to affect the enjoyment of others.  IE, dont be an arse-butthead-moron.<br>
<br>
Etc etc. <p>Sharak'Duom 51 Ghost<br>
Keroppi'Duom 60 Godzilla<br>
Sharakai'Duom 59 Ronin</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usharak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharak</A> at: 7/3/02 10:03:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wychway>Wychway</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/4/02 10:03:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What Makes A Good Warrior?</span><hr size=1> Be easily distractable!! *snicker*<br>
