</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kudil>Kudil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/5/02 2:29:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=950.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What Makes A Good Warrior?</span><hr size=1> Competance.  Know what mobs are in the area, and how things agro.  Know if you can solo pull, agro ranges, chain agro ranges, basically, know everything you can about the zones you hunt in.  Have a good sense of humor, but be serious when necessary.<br>
<br>
Push your group to the limit.... Not to the point of bieng suicidal but, Exp is boring... Anyone who says they enjoy exping is either lying or in need of help.  So you do what you can to liven it up.  What I used to do is run my cleric/warrior/monk and solo bk/captain camps in Chardok.. friends of mine would be without a group so would run down to join me... and to keep it lively, we would pull just about everything we could, oftentimes nearly to the point of wiping out.  Sometimes we did, most times we didnt.  It keeps you aware, and makes it not so damned boring...<br>
<br>
And if all else fails... run bots!<br>
<br>
Oh, and don't taunt before breaking mezzes, chanters love that. (or you can use it as a form of discipline if they get mouthy!) <p><a target = new href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64016">~Kudil 60 Warrior</a>
